publicationXreff1a.standardName: Gremlin, Noggin, Chordin and follistatin differentially modulate BMP induced suppression of androgen secretion by bovine ovarian theca cells.

comments.content:
This integrated pathway shows cross-talk among circadian rhythm, autophagy and osteoclast/osteoblast differentiation pathways. 
Other pathways are shown as activators and/or inhibitors of the bone remodeling process.
